FastAPI Monitoring System (Prometheus + Grafana)
This project provides a centralized monitoring system for FastAPI applications using:

Prometheus → Metrics collection & storage
Grafana → Visualization dashboards
Node Exporter → Server resource monitoring
The system tracks:

Total API hits Endpoint-wise requests HTTP method usage Server CPU / Memory metrics

Architecture Overview
FastAPI App
     │
     │ /metrics
     ▼
Prometheus (Scrapes Metrics)
     │
     ▼
Grafana (Dashboard Visualization)
Monitoring Components
Service	Purpose
FastAPI	Exposes application metrics
Prometheus	Collects & stores metrics
Grafana	Displays graphs & dashboards
Node Exporter	System metrics (CPU/RAM/Disk)
FastAPI Metrics Implementation
app/main.py
from fastapi import FastAPI
from prometheus_client import Counter, generate_latest, CONTENT_TYPE_LATEST
from starlette.responses import Response

app = FastAPI()

REQUEST_COUNT = Counter(
    "app_requests_total",
    "Total HTTP Requests",
    ["method", "endpoint"]
)

@app.middleware("http")
async def count_requests(request, call_next):
    response = await call_next(request)

    REQUEST_COUNT.labels(
        method=request.method,
        endpoint=request.url.path
    ).inc()

    return response


@app.get("/")
def home():
    return {"message": "Hello World"}


@app.get("/metrics")
def metrics():
    return Response(generate_latest(), media_type=CONTENT_TYPE_LATEST)
What this does
Counts every API request

Labels requests by:

HTTP Method
Endpoint
Exposes metrics at:

http://SERVER_IP:8000/metrics
Prometheus Configuration
prometheus.yml
global:
  scrape_interval: 15s

scrape_configs:
  - job_name: 'fastapi_apps'
    static_configs:
      - targets:
          - 172.16.5.7:8000

  - job_name: 'node_exporters'
    static_configs:
      - targets:
          - 172.16.5.7:9100
Explanation
Config	Meaning
scrape_interval	Collect metrics every 15 seconds
fastapi_apps	Scrapes FastAPI /metrics
node_exporters	Scrapes server metrics
Running the Monitoring Stack
Start monitoring services:

docker compose up -d
Services:

Service	URL
FastAPI	http://172.16.5.7:8000
Prometheus	http://172.16.5.7:9090
Grafana	http://172.16.5.7:3000
Access Grafana
Open:

http://172.16.5.7:3000
Default login:

Username: admin
Password: admin
Add Prometheus Data Source
Go to Settings → Data Sources
Add Prometheus
URL:
http://prometheus:9090
Click Save & Test
View Total API Hits
Create Dashboard:

Dashboards → Create Dashboard → Add Panel
Switch query mode to Code.

Total API Hits
sum(app_requests_total)
Shows total requests received by FastAPI.

Useful Queries
Total Hits
sum(app_requests_total)
Hits Per Endpoint
sum by (endpoint)(app_requests_total)
Hits Per HTTP Method
sum by (method)(app_requests_total)
Requests Per Second (Production Metric)
rate(app_requests_total[1m])
Generate Test Traffic
Open API multiple times:

http://172.16.5.7:8000/
or

curl http://172.16.5.7:8000/
Metrics will increase automatically.

🗄 Data Storage
Prometheus stores metrics locally using TSDB.

Retention example:

--storage.tsdb.retention.time=60d
Stores monitoring data for 2 months.

